        Official Singles Chart on 8/1/2021

        8 January 2021 - 14 January 2021

        The Official Singles Chart Top 100 reflects the UKs biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1. View the biggest songs of 2025.

        Okay, so instead of my weekly chart review this week (because there was no way I was going to cover everything in one review), here's my reordering for the Chart Of 2020! :D

        I'll post this on the EOY Chart page too.

        One thing I want to stress is that the ratings for these songs are heavily influenced by personal influence & replay factor. In particular, some of the hits that weren't released in 2020 will get a lower score than the song's quality truly represents!

        So, for example, 'All It Want For Christmas Is You' deserves higher than a 8/10, but it's getting knocked down here because it appears in the chart every year & this Christmas wasn't really a situation where I wanted to hear it.

        That being said, songs like 'Sunflower' are boosted, because I recall back to memories where I really enjoyed hearing it on the radio & the fact that it has aged really well as a hit. That's why it'll be ranking fairly high in this case!

        I'll post the list above shortly, so be prepared for a long post, but either way, it's just my opinion, so please be respectful.
